properties.Name: PalletType
properties.Description:
A pallet is a flat transport structure that supports goods in a stable fashion while being lifted by a forklift, pallet jack, front loader, work saver or other jacking device. A pallet is the structural foundation of a unit load which allows handling and storage efficiencies. Goods or shipping containers are often placed on a pallet secured with strapping, stretch wrap or shrink wrap and shipped.

Ex.:
- Block Pallet
- Double-Face Pallet
- Double-Wing Pallet
- Flush Pallet
- Four-way Stringer Pallet
- Non-Reversible Pallet
- Reversible Pallet
- Single-Wing Pallet
- Skid Pallet
- Solid Deck Pallet
- Two-Way Entry Pallet
- Two-Way Stringer Pallet

Columns.Name: PalletTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Pallet Type.

Columns.Name: ItemSku
Columns.Description: The Stock Keeping Unit identifier, which is typically used for inventory-related activities.

Columns.Name: PalletTypeName
Columns.Description: The name of the Pallet Type.

Columns.Name: PalletTypeDescription
Columns.Description: The description of the Pallet Type.

Columns.Name: InformationLabelText
Columns.Description:
The label text that identifies the care, use, preparation and handling or the pallet.

Examples:
- "Keep out of direct sunlight..."
- "Keep out of reach of children..."

Columns.Name: DescriptiveLabelText
Columns.Description: The label text that describes significant characteristics and benefits.

Columns.Name: WarningInformationText
Columns.Description: The text of the warning label, if any, appearing upon the pallet.

Columns.Name: GradeLabelText
Columns.Description:
The label text that identifies pallet quality with letters, number or conditions.

Examples:

-  Grade A
-  Prime
-  #1

Columns.Name: UniversalProductCode
Columns.Description:
A system that identifies products by type and by manufacturer.  

A UPC consists of eleven (11) digits.  Six (6) indicate the Manufacturer and five (5) digits describe the product.

UPCs appear on product packages as bar codes, which are graphic symbols that are read by optical scanner devices.   

UPCs are assigned by the Uniform Code Council of Dayton, Ohio.

Columns.Name: EuropeanArticleNumber
Columns.Description:
A 13 digit barcoding standard which is a superset of the original 12-digit Universal Product Code (UPC).

aka International Article Number (abbreviation of EAN retained)

Columns.Name: GlobalTradeItemNumber
Columns.Description: The Global Trade Item Number (GTIN) is an identifier for trade items that was developed by GS1.

Columns.Name: ItemElectronicProductCode
Columns.Description:
EPC is the RFID version of the UPC barcode. 
EPC is intended to be used for specific product identification. However, EPC goes beyond UPC by not only identifying the product as an SKU, but also providing access to additional data about the origin and history of the specific units. 
The EPC tag itself identifies the manufacturer, product, version, and serial number. It's the serial number that takes EPC to the next level. 
This is the key to data related to specific lots/batches as well as potentially tracking the specific unit's history as it moves through the supply chain.

Columns.Name: ComponentPartIdentifier
Columns.Description: The Component / Part Identifier (CPID) is used to identify components or parts that are used in the assembly of a larger item. The CPID is part of the GS1 system of standards.

Columns.Name: GlobalReturnableAssetIdentifier
Columns.Description:
The Global Returnable Asset Identifier (GRAI) was developed by GS1 to be used to identify assets by type. It can also be used to uniquely identify assets by including the serial number. 

The GRAI is used to identify Returnable Transport Items (RTI) such as pallets, roll container, crates. The GRAI identifies the type of returnable asset.

Columns.Name: PalletNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the pallet.

Columns.Name: PalletLength
Columns.Description: The length of the Pallet.

Columns.Name: PalletWidth
Columns.Description: The width of the Pallet.

Columns.Name: PalletHeight
Columns.Description: The height of the Pallet.

Columns.Name: LwhUomId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Unit Of Measure.

Columns.Name: PalletWeight
Columns.Description: The weight of the Pallet.

Columns.Name: WeightUomId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Unit Of Measure.

Columns.Name: SerializedPalletIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the Pallet is serialized.

Columns.Name: OwningPartyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Party.

Columns.Name: DepositRequiredIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that a deposit is required for using this type of pallet.

Columns.Name: RentalIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that a the pallet is to be rented.

Columns.Name: SingleUseIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that a the pallet is to be used one time / is not reusable.
